login process is bugged. need to go out of vr to activate then login again and once you do this is says object not found. came back in the software I had t restart the software because it seemed crashed. After restart i refused to go in the painfull process of juste entering you email.So not wasting my time more than this.

Very nice to watch all kinds of virtual scenario's people made, but if you want to start creating yourself - and as a teacher in training I would love to do so - grab out that creditcard and pay at least 89$ a month. The free trial is so limited in functionality you can hardly use it for educational purposes and sorry, I can't afford 89$ a month  as a student for some software. You could compare it with YouTube saying 'Come and watch great content, but if you want to upload your own movies you have to pay.'  I hate it when companies trick you this way, and that's why I'am giving only 1 star.
Haen't had a chance to play much but my first thoughts are so so
